The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Business Briefs

 New Delhi, Aug. 23: Maharashtra will seek a compensation of Rs 250 crore from the Centre for less revenue generation due to value-added tax (VAT) for the first quarter of this fiscal. The state collected Rs 2,451 crore from VAT items during the period against a projection of Rs 2,701 crore, Maharashtra sales tax commissioner B.C. Khatua said after a VAT panel meeting today. Under the compensation formulae, states will be compensated fully this fiscal if their revenue falls short of projection. The projection is calculated on the basis of weighted average of sales tax revenue during the best three of the last five years.

 Mumbai, Aug. 23: The Reserve Bank (RBI) has simplified the know your customer (KYC) procedure for people from low-income group opening accounts in urban co-operative banks. It has allowed acceptance of introduction from another account holder who has been subjected to the full KYC procedure. The guidelines are for account holders whose balance will not exceed Rs 50,000 in all the accounts taken together. The total credit in all the accounts should also not exceed Rs 1 lakh in a year, the RBI said in a notification. 

 Mumbai, Aug. 23: Sasken Communications Technologies Ltd has fixed the issue price for its initial public offering at Rs 260 per share. The company had offered 50 lakh shares at a face value of Rs 10 each. Enam Financial Consultants Pvt Ltd was the sole book-running lead manager to the issue.

 New Delhi, Aug. 23: The government will sell two-year bonds with a coupon rate of 11.90 per cent on August 25 for raising Rs 6,000 crore under the market stabilisation scheme.

 New Delhi, Aug. 23: The infrastructure growth plummeted to 0.5 per cent in July compared with 11.1 per cent a year ago, owing to a drop in the production of coal, steel, power and crude.

 Bangalore, Aug. 23: Motorola Inc has identified India as an R amp;D base and plans to hire 1,000 people by next year, chairman and CEO Edward Zander said today.




